The paper discusses the importance of feature selection and interpretation in machine learning, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of kernel machines and deep neural networks, which are popular techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the non-linear nature of the proposed feature importance measure, which is relevant to the subfield of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms (cs.NE). Lastly, the paper mentions the use of instance-based feature importance, which is a topic in the subfield of similarity-based learning and instance-based learning (cs.SI).
